headline: HIGH COURT DEFERS BIRTH CONTROL TEST; Refuses to Discuss Jurisdiction Involving Case Under Connecticut Law WIDE INTEREST IN SUIT But Tribunal Says Physician Sponsored Test Instead of 3 Women Concerned
snippet: WASHINGTON, Feb. 1 -- Because of the circumstances under which the case was put to the Supreme Court, the tribunal today refused to discuss whether it had jurisdiction to pass upon the validity of the Connecticut Birth Control Law.
